hopobject.body: I'm only getting an answering machine thedrugstorelimited.com One of the two Eagle sisters, Maria Eagle was elected to the shadow cabinet back in October 2010 and was made Shadow Transport Secretary by Ed Miliband. She successfully dropped Labour’s policy on Heathrow expansion, and more controversially called for a state railway company to be able to bid for network franchises. As the Government puts more emphasis on infrastructure investment, Eagle will have one of the most important jobs in opposition.
